The paper presents a novel Bayesian matrix completion method based on spectral regularization, which involves low-rank matrix factorization and collaborative filtering. These topics are commonly studied in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
